_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.1: Check this box if you are the head of household filing for your entire family unit.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.2: Write your personal seal (hanko/inkan) impression in this box - if you don't have a registered seal, you may be able to use a signature instead depending on your municipality.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.3: Check this box if you are a family member filing for only part of your household (not the entire family).
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.4: Check this box if you are moving out of the current address to a location outside the ward/city.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.5: Fill in your name using katakana characters in the thick-bordered box provided.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.6: This note indicates that if you are not a member of the same household as the person you're filing for, you need a power of attorney document.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.7: Write your phone number in this field so the office can contact you if there are any questions about your application.
_vision_explanations:Who Is Filing:2f293.8: Check the appropriate box for your situation: 世帯 (whole household), 転入 (moving in), 特例 (special case), 一部 (partial household), 転出 (moving out), or 転居 (moving within the same ward/city).

_vision_explanations:Footer & Notes:0215.3: Circle or check the appropriate method for how this form will be handled - whether it's being hand-delivered (手渡し), mailed (郵送), being corrected (修正), collected (回収), or if an envelope has been provided (封筒渡済). This is typically marked by office staff rather than the applicant.
